---
source: src/cli/mod.rs
assertion: completion generates deterministic shell completion scripts
schema:
  output: shell-completion-script
  supported_shells: bash, zsh, fish, powershell, elvish
contracts:
  - completion generates shell-specific completion scripts via clap_complete
  - bash completions include complete -F bindings
  - zsh completions include compdef and _arguments
  - fish completions include complete -c bindings
  - output is deterministic for a given shell type
  - no JSON output (raw shell script text)
  - exit code 0 on success
evidence:
  - CompletionArgs.shell
  - clap_complete::generate()
  - Shell::Bash, Shell::Zsh, Shell::Fish, Shell::PowerShell, Shell::Elvish
